        \nI.  DEFINITION
        \n I.1 “This Agreement” refers to this User Service Agreement and its amendments from time to time.
        \n I.2 "Cold Storage" refers to the hardware products that realize the secure storage of digital assets based on hierarchical deterministic (HD) technology. Cold Storage uses two technical schemes to generate Private Keys in different currencies, one is to randomly generate seed passwords and set Payment Passwords, and the seed passwords are combined with Payment Passwords to generate Private Keys in different currencies. The other is to generate Mnemonic words randomly, and the Private Keys of different currencies are generated by Mnemonic words. Finally, the Public Key is generated by the Private Key, and the asset address is generated by the Public Key to realize the secure storage of digital assets.
        \n I.3 "Hot Storage" refers to digital asset storages developed based on blockchain, including other auxiliary tools developed to facilitate User to use blockchain systems.
        \n I.4 "Public key" refers to the one-way derivation of the Private Key with the help of the principle of cryptography, and is used to generate the blockchain digital storage address, which is the public collection address.
        \n I.5 "Private key" refers to a 256-bit random character, which is the key for users to own and use digital assets.
        \n I.6 "Mnemonic Word" refers to the 12 (or 15/18/21/24) ordered words generated by a random algorithm that comply with the blockchain BIP39 industry standard. It is an easy-to-record expression of the Private Key, which is convenient for User to backup and keep.
        \n I.7 "Payment Password" refers to a password that the User should set during the process of creating a storage, which will be used in conjunction with the seed password to generate a currency Private Key. This password cannot be modified, and once the User loses or forgets the password, the asset will not be recovered.
        \n I.8 "Security Password" refers to a password that the User should set during the process of creating a storage, which will be used to protect the Private Key. The Security Password is not stored in the User\'s mobile device or the Platform server, and once the User forgets the password, it will not be recovered. The User can use the Private Key or Mnemonic Word to re-import the storage and set a new Security Password.
